1. Wyoming, USA, launches public chain bidding for stablecoin issuance and publicizes the review process;
2.5 Chainlink non-circulating supply addresses have deposited 17.855 million LINK to Binance in the past 10 hours;
3. Musk's xAI offers investors more favorable pricing for $5 billion debt issuance;
4. The current unrealized profit of a "bottom-long, top-short" ETH smart money has exceeded $14.8 million;
5. A whale deposited 10 million USDC into Hyperliquid to purchase HYPE;
6. Paradigm has liquidated 70 million LDOs, making a profit of $28.13 million in a four-year cycle;
7. Binance: Users with at least 251 Alpha points can apply for the first phase of Redbrick (BRIC) airdrops;
8. Bitdeer: The total holdings of Bitcoin have exceeded 1,445;
9. Viewpoint: The current bull market cycle may continue until Second quarter of 2026.

Odaily Planet Daily News According to the Hong Kong Ta Kung Pao, the Hong Kong Economic and Trade Union Federation released a research report on building a global stable currency issuance center, proposing six strategic suggestions to support the construction of a global stable currency issuance center: 
1. Build a global stable currency issuance center; 
2. Improve regulatory protection risks and improve the efficiency of pilot projects; 
3. Develop offshore RMB stable currencies; 
4. Expand the size of Hong Kong's RMB funding pool; 
5. Promote colleges and universities to strengthen financial technology courses; 
6. Establish a high-level financial development committee to coordinate and communicate with mainland financial departments to discuss in-depth financial connectivity between the two places.
